<br>
DB 1000, DI 1<br>
<br>
min hit of 1001 non defensive, max hit of 1020 no defensive<br>
min hit of 1001(1000.5) defensive, max hit of 1010 defensive<br>
<br>
Using /disc def did almost nothing to reduce the damage taken. If you assume that evasive will make you avoid 10% of those hits, it just saved you a ton of damage.<br>
<br>
<br>
DB 1, DI 100<br>
<br>
min hit of 101 non defensive, max hit of 2001 non defensive<br>
min hit of 51 defensive, max hit of 1001 defensive<br>
<br>
Using /disc def cut your damage by half. Using evasive would lower the damage taken, but not nearly as dramatically as defensive would in this case.<br>
<br>
Defensive is best when tanking a mob that has a high DI and low DB, relative to each other. Due to the fact that the DB cannot be mitigated at all, it is best to simply not get hit (use evasive) on mobs that a very high DB relative to the DI.<br>
